Definition: Something distressing that it causes one to lose all hope of faith.  Origin: From Shakespeare's Measure for Measure...man ,/Drest in a little brief authority,/plays such fantastic tricks before high heaven/As make the angles weep.
Example: For several years the government has continuously reduce the amount of money spent on education.  Now they complain that teachers are not doing their job properly-It's enough to make the angels weep.